<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
1.8-2.0 mm long (mean = 1.88 mm; n = 5); 2.57-3.0
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the declivital face with interstriae 2 unarmed by tubercles; elytral apex attenuated, with three (usually) pairs of large flattened tubercles; and declivital interstriae flat, interstriae 2 not impressed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
